<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16997] OTEL configurator NPE when SOLR_HOST not set</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16997</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you start Solr 9.3 with OTEL tracing enabled, but do not set SOLR_HOST, solr will not come up due to it trying to read sysprop &quot;host&quot; which is null and &lt;tt&gt;Map.of()&lt;/tt&gt; requires non-null key and value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Simple workaround is to set SOLR_HOST but for dev environment it would be nice to fix the bug by checking before setting the &quot;host.name&quot; trace-property.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
at java.base/java.util.Objects.requireNonNull(Unknown Source)
java.lang.NullPointerException: &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
at java.util.Objects.requireNonNull(Unknown Source) ~[?:?]
at java.util.ImmutableCollections$Map1.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(Unknown Source) ~[?:?]
at java.util.Map.of(Unknown Source) ~[?:?]
at org.apache.solr.opentelemetry.OtelTracerConfigurator.getTracer(OtelTracerConfigurator.java:50) ~[?:?] &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
